gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 138, Lakers 94
gameRecap.excerpt: Joel Embiid led the 76ers with 30 points, 11 rebounds, and 11 assists in his first triple-double of the year and sixth of his career. Tyrese Maxey (31 points, eight assists) and Marcus Morris Sr. (16 points) totaled 47 points for the 76ers, who shot 22-46 from beyond the arc. LeBron James led the Lakers with 18 points while Anthony Davis totaled 17 points and 11 rebounds. The 76ers improve to 12-5 on the year as the Lakers move to 10-8.
